Grezz Goodsmith<br>
Knight of the Emerald Phoenix <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bluclin71335.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=irulanicorrino>Irulani Corrino</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/15/01 12:29:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=821.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What to get your opnion on a great idea by Raventod</span><hr size=1> WIll I raid vox/naggy in the future    Of course I will. Will I host one. Probally far in the future, anf probally not with Irulani<br>
<br>
I have seem my friends play EQ since it's inseption, playing vicariously thru them and by listening them talk about it. Reading nad hearing about a game is far different than actaully palying it... for years. That basically makes a well-versed noob.<br>
<br>
You say that I am greedy. If keeping a scale I won and wont give it up is greed, then I must be. IF taking steps to ensure you own sucess is greed, then I must be. But realize that you do not know me well enough to make _any sort of generalizations about my character or honor.<br>
<br>
When I first won the scale, I got TONS of msg'ing asking me if I would sell it or give them/someone else, and yes Forsakenn was one of them. What I said then still holds true:<br>
I was very lucky to have won the scale at all, and I do not wish to test fate again. This is why<br>
<br>
