<br>
But I think thatwas my turning point in the game, I went from pissing people off and being a solo as much as I can player, to a team player that as often as I can I help others get group built to take on their epic mobs...<br>
<br>
I just now finally made level 53 after I completed my epic, with huge amounts of help from many people, I have a journal stock full of many names I won't remember unless I look through it, and I look through it pretty much every week, and I add to it every day....<br>
<br>
Now your right at level 42 his contribution had to be minor when you got to naggy, but against the rest of the foes that took 90% of the raids time, he was a very effective force I am certain. I wonder if he brought any friends with him to that raid, and I am certain he would be a friend to everyone at that raid if they ever gave him a shot. A year from now you will ALL be in the same place anyways.. level 60 wondering what to do with your time...<br>
<br>
thats just my feelings... I think epics are what turn solo players into leaders of many. I still have alot of work to be a great leader, but I try hard, and do my best to keep everyone happy and on track. <p>Sivana
